AD_ELEMENT.NAME: By Default Allow Filtering

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: It defines it the filter is allowed. If it is set, all the elements within the system will take this value as the default one.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Report Definition
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Report Definition of a Process Definition created as Report.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: PDF Template
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: JRXML PDF Template

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Excel Template
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: JRXML template to export to Excel the report when a specific template is required for excel

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Use PDF as Excel Template
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Determines whether the PDF Template needs to be used to generate the Excel report instead of defining a specific template for it.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Navigation Bar Component Role Access
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines which roles have access to which navigation bar components.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines which roles have access to which navigation bar components.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Use PDF as HTML Template
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Determines whether the PDF Template needs to be used to generate the HTML report instead of defining a specific template for it.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Determines whether the PDF Template needs to be used to generate the HTML report instead of defining a specific template for it.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Lazy Filtering on Grid
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If it is set, the grid won't perform a filter and/or a sorting action until the 'Apply Filters' button be pressed. In the same way, the summary functions present in the grid won't be recalculated until this button be pressed.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If it is set, the grid won't perform a filter and/or a sorting action until the 'Apply Filters' button be pressed. In the same way, the summary functions present in the grid won't be recalculated until this button be pressed.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Disable Foreign Key Combo
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If this flag is checked, the foreign key combo will be disabled and the column will be filtered like a standard text column
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If this flag is checked, the foreign key combo will be disabled and the column will be filtered like a standard text column

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Compatibility with Legacy Grids
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This flags is used to specify if this process should be compatible with the legacy parameter windows.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Unfiltered Foreign Key Combo
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If this flag if checked, the filter drop down will show the rows from the referenced table unfiltered by specific rows being referenced in the referencing table.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If this flag if checked, the filter drop down will show the rows from the referenced table unfiltered by specific rows being referenced in the referencing table. The filters entered by the user in the grid filter editor will be applied.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: On Grid Load Function
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This function is invoked when the grid parameter is loaded for the first time.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This function is invoked when the grid parameter is loaded for the first time.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Obuiapp_Data_Pool_Sel_ID
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Data pool selection for Reports
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Holds the relationship between a report and the database pool where its data will be fetched.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Summary Function
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines the summary function to use, valid values: sum, avg, max, min, count

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: New Function
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines the function that will called when adding a new row to the grid

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Number of Displayed Rows
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The height of the grid will be adjusted to display the number of rows specified in this field.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The height of the grid will be adjusted to display the number of rows specified in this field.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Validation Function
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines the function to be used as part of fields validatiors
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: By default a field have a set of validation functions, isNumber, isBoolean, etc. The developer can define a custom validator function to check the value entered by a the user.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Sorting
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: It defines it the sort is allowed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If it is set, it will overwrite the system defaults.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Multi Record
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Allow execution on multiple records at the same time
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Multi Record allows to execute the process in multiple records at the same time. When this flag is set, multiple records can be selected in grid mode and the process can be executed in all of them at the same time.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Available for All Roles
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines that this navigation bar component is available to all roles or that role access is defined specifically by role.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines that this navigation bar component is available to all roles or that role access is defined specifically by role through the navigation bar role access table.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Column Number
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Column number in which the current field is set (allowed values ​​between 1 and 4)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Column number in which the current field is set (allowed values ​​between 1 and 4)

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Remove Function
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Function that will get executed when removing a row from the grid
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When the grid allows remove rows you can specify a "on remove" function that will get executed when trying remove a row. If the function returns false, the row will not get removed.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Logger
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Logger name
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Name used to identify a Logger. It usually corresponds to the name of the class being logged, but it can also be named using an arbitrary name.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Property Path
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines the property path taken for this parameter.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines the property path taken for this parameter.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Classname of the view implementation
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The java class name of the view implementation. The java class must extend the org.openbravo.client.kernel.BaseTemplateComponent.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The java class name of the view implementation. The java class must extend the org.openbravo.client.kernel.BaseTemplateComponent.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Process Defintion
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Process Defintion
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Process Defintion is a re implementation of Process with 3.0 infrastructure.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Value Key
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Column to store ID values.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Column to store ID values of Foreign Key parameters and Search Key of List parameters.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Show Summary
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Show Summary
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines if the Field should show a summary function at the end of the grid

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Can Delete
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines if a user is allowed to delete lines
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines if a user is allowed to delete lines

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Summary Functions
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If this flag is enabled then the user can add summary functions into the grid, by using the column header context menu. If not enabled, then the summary functions menu will not be available.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If this flag is enabled then the user can add summary functions into the grid, by using the column header context menu. If not enabled, then the summary functions menu will not be available.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: HTML Template
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: JRXML template to use for exporting the report to HTML format
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: JRXML template to use for exporting the report to HTML format

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Navigation Bar Component
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A component shown in the navigation bar in the top of the user interface
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A navigation bar component is a component which is shown in the navigation bar in the top of the user interface. For example a quick create or an application menu.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Show In Description
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines if this parameter is relevant in Text column on C_File table.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines if this parameter is relevant in Text column on C_File table.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Transactional Filters
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If this flag is enabled then the transactional filters will be enabled. If not enabled. then all the transactional filters will be disabled.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If this flag is enabled then the transactional filters will be enabled. A transactional filter is the filter that is applied by default when a transactional window is accessed. It filters all the documents with status Draft or which date is in the defined "Transaction Range". If not enabled. then all the transactional filters will be disabled.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: View Implementation
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The view implementation which is shown in the tab of a multi-document-interface
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The view implementation which is shown in the tab of a multi-document-interface.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Can Add
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines if a user is allowed to add new lines
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines if a user is allowed to add new lines

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Evaluate Fixed Value
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When the flag is enabled the Fixed Value is evaluated as a JS expression.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Selection Function
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Custom JavaScript function that will get executed when the selection in a grid changes
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When the user changes the selection (a row gets selected or deselected) the custom JavaScript function will get executed

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Report
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: References a report regardless the place it is defined
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: References a report regardless the place it is defined

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: On Refresh Function
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: In this field a javascript function can be defined. This function will be executed when the parameter window refresh action be invoked.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
In this field a javascript function can be defined. This function will be executed when the parameter window refresh action be invoked. For example, if the process has a child-process, once the child-process finishes, it will invoke a refresh of the parent process.
Since each process has its particularities, a custom refresh function should be defined in case the process be susceptible of being refreshed/reloaded.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Process Definition
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Process to be executed by the button
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Process to be executed by the button. There are 2 kinds of processes: *"Process": Implements the 2.50 style processes with a Servlet. *"Process Definition": Implements 3.0 processes with a pure SmartClient UI.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Filtering
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: It defines it the filter is allowed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If it is set, it will overwrite the system defaults.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Selection Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: It specifies the selection type that will apply to the grid
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: It specifies the selection type that will apply to the grid. Its value can be: * "None": no rows can be selected * "Single": only one row can be selected * "Multiple": multiple rows can be selected

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Threshold to Trigger Filter on Text Field (in ms)
AD_ELEMENT.PRINTNAME: Threshold to Trigger Filter on Text Field (in ms)
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Threshold in ms to trigger filter on text field
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Threshold in miliseconds to trigger the filter on text fields

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Colspan
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Number of columns this field should occupy in the form
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This value can be used to define, multi-columns fields. So fields occupying more then one column. If this value is not set the normal calculation takes place.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Data Pool
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Lists all possible database pools which OBDal can use to retrieve data.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Lists all possible database pools which OBDal can use to retrieve data.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: By Default Allow Sorting
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: It defines it the sort is allowed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: It defines it the sort is allowed. If it is set, all the elements within the system will take this value as the default one.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Static Component
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines whether a navigation bar component is static or not.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines whether a navigation bar component is static or not. Static components are generated in the same request of the session dynamic resources. Non static components requires an extra request call to generate its content.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Show Select Column
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines if the select column should be shown
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Some use cases requires that the selection column (checkbox column) is hidden

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Log Level
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Logger log level
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the minimum level events should have for this Logger to process them. By default this level is determined by the config files: it is inherited from the root logger unless an specific configuration for this class/package is defined.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: On Load Function
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: In this field a javascript function can be defined. This function will be executed when the parameter window is loaded, just after the default values are set.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: In this field a javascript function can be defined. This function will be executed when the parameter window is loaded, just after the default values are set.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Navigation Bar Classname
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The classname of the navigation bar component.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The java class name of the navigation bar component. The java class must extend the org.openbravo.client.kernel.BaseTemplateComponent.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Text Filter Behavior
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines the kind of filter that will be applied by default to text fields

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Show Title
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This field allows to specify whether the title of a grid form item should be displayed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This field allows to specify whether the title of a grid form item should be displayed

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Filtering Foreign Keys by its Identifier
AD_ELEMENT.PRINTNAME: Allow Filtering Foreign Keys by its iIdentifier
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If this flag is checked, then the user can filter foreign keys either by selecting some options from the filter drop down or by entering text manually.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If this flag is checked, then the user can filter foreign keys either by selecting some options from the filter drop down or by entering text manually. If this flag is unchecked, then the foreign keys would only be filterable by selecting some options from the filter drop down, which has better performance.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Client Side Validation
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: JavaScript function to be executed before invoking the backend Handler.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: JavaScript function to be executed before invoking the backend Handler. This function (manually coded), can: - Perform validations on the parameters, being possible to prevent execution in case these validations are not satisfied. - Request for additional info to complete the parameter values.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Text Field Filter Behavior
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines the kind of filter that will be applied to this item. It only works with text fields.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Defines the kind of filter (iContains, iStartsWith, etc) that will be applied to this item. It only works with text fields.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Filter On Change
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If this flag is checked, text columns will trigger a filter on change
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If this flag is checked, text columns will trigger a filter each time its content changes.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Rowspan
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Number of rows this field should occupy in the form
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This value can be used to define, multi-row fields. So fields occupying more then one row. If this value is not set the normal calculation takes place.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Can Add Records to a Selector
AD_ELEMENT.PRINTNAME: Can Add Records to a Selector
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: By selecting this flag, the process will be available in the 'Defined Selector' window
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: By selecting this flag, the process will be available in the 'Defined Selector' window. This process has to be capable of adding records to a selector.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default Filter Expression
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines a expression used to filter the property
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
Defines a JavaScript expression that will be evaluated in the server side and used as default value for the property. You can use any type of variable but it must match the property type, examples:
true - the property associated is a boolean "Hello" - the property associated is a string 5.3 - the property associated is a number
You can also access the API through the OB object and do some more complex expressions, e.g.
OB.getSession().getAttribute("SESSIONVAR");
This will retrieve the session variable SESSIONVAR and use it as default value for the filter of this field.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: View Implementation
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines the implementation of a view shown in the user interface.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A view is displayed inside a tab in the multi document interface.
